# Next.js Standards — `apps/web`

## App Router Conventions
- **Default to Server Components**. Add `"use client"` only when needed (hooks, browser APIs, event handlers).
- File-based routing lives in `app/`. Use `layout.tsx`, `page.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx` per segment.
- Fetch data directly in Server Components — no `useEffect` for data loading.
- Use **Server Actions** for mutations instead of separate API route handlers.

```tsx
// ✅ Server Component with direct data fetch
export default async function UsersPage() {
  const users = await getUsers()  // direct DB/API call, no useEffect
  return <UserList users={users} />
}
```

```tsx
// ✅ Client Component — only when needed
"use client"
export function SearchInput({ onSearch }: { onSearch: (q: string) => void }) {
  return <input onChange={(e) => onSearch(e.target.value)} />
}
```

## TailwindCSS (v4)
- Use Tailwind utility classes exclusively — no inline `style={{}}`, no CSS Modules for new code.
- Design mobile-first: base styles for mobile, `sm:` / `md:` / `lg:` for larger screens.
- Use `@repo/tailwind-config` shared styles; import `@repo/ui/styles.css` in the root `layout.tsx`.
- Group related utilities: layout → spacing → typography → color → interaction.

```tsx
// ✅
<button className="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white bg-indigo-600 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-700 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-500">
  Save
</button>
```

## Components
- Shared, reusable components belong in `packages/ui` (imported as `@repo/ui`), not in `apps/web`.
- Page-specific components live co-located inside their route segment folder.
- Use semantic HTML: `<main>`, `<section>`, `<nav>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`, `<article>`.
- Every interactive element must be keyboard-accessible and have an accessible label.

## TypeScript
- Extends `@repo/typescript-config/nextjs.json` — `strict`, `noEmit`, bundler module resolution.
- Run `next typegen` before `tsc --noEmit` (already in `check-types` script).
- Explicitly type all `props` interfaces; avoid `React.FC<>` — prefer plain function signatures.

```tsx
// ✅
interface UserCardProps {
  user: { id: string; name: string; email: string }
}
export function UserCard({ user }: UserCardProps) { ... }
```

## Dev Server
- Runs on **port 3003** (`bun dev` from repo root or `apps/web`).
- Environment variables are loaded from `.env` files; prefix public vars with `NEXT_PUBLIC_`.
